Cell.Data: PAC identifier for the parent of the PAC unit
It describes the assembly from which the element is obtained.
PAC identifier for the action of the PAC unit
It provides a unique identifier for each action.
It describes the action that need to be performed.
It provides a detailed explanation of the disassembly action that needs to be performed.
It provides the number of times the action must be performed. It is applicable only for screws and/or repeated processes.
It describes the tool required to perform the action.
PAC identifier for the child of the PAC unit
It describes the element that are obtained as output of the action.
It describes the number of the same child obtained from the disassembly action.
It provides a unique identifier for each disassembly action.
It explained the effect of the DF on the action (i.e., the disassembly process).
It describes the disassembly type that must be performed due to the DF. It can be: i) destructive, ii) semi-destructive, iii) no destructive
It describes the tool that needs to be used in order to perform the disassembly action
It provides what type of disassembly error has happened either DF1, DF2 or DF3.
